Losing a child makes you reflect. Who do I want my kids to be? How do I want them to interact with the world, and how do I make sure they grow up to be solid humans? To gain grit, resiliency, humility, integrity, character, kindness, honesty. Nature can teach you so many of these things which is why @morganebeck and I decided to expand on the lives we live in Southern California and provide the balance of Big Sky, MT. We are thrilled to be making the move to Big Sky part time and making more of life @spanishpeaksmountainclub. Thank you to @tetongravity for capturing my story so beautifully. To watch the full film click the link in my bio

Awareness is something I wish I had before we lost Emmy. Awareness that drowning is the number one cause of death for children under the age of 5. Awareness of the preventative measures available to keep her safe. Awareness that a majority of drownings happen during non swim times. Awareness of the false sense of security I was creating for her by putting on her puddle jumper. I wish it didn’t take the price of losing Emmy for me to understand the truth about drowning. Let my lessons be yours. Multiple layers of protection around water should be mandatory (door locks, door alarms, pool fences, @coralmanta drowning detection pool alarms and survival swim lessons @infantswimmingresource) We can end drowning #hadIknownthenwhatIknownow #drowningprevention
Zone defence, like the Falcons.

Thank you for creating a system to help us end drowning and keep our babies safe! Every layer of protection matters. 
Going Beyond the Pool Alarm!: The downside of pool alarms is that they are often turned off when people can use the pool, but then never turned back on. Likewise, if it’s the case of a supervised pool where a child goes under, a pool alarm won’t matter. Enter the Coral Manta 3000, a drowning detection device that uses an underwater camera and artificial intelligence (AI) to alert people if there’s a problem. The camera monitors swimmers’ motion in the pool, while the AI system is trained to look for dangerous behavior. If it detects no movement from a swimmer after 15 seconds, it sends an alert to your phone app.

For many months I have been searching for a solution that can help prevent families from going through the loss and pain that we have suffered.
Layers of protection are a must and the Coral Manta 3000 is one of best layers I have seen. It is the a new, revolutionary, AI / Computer Vision based 24/7 drowning detection system for residential pools.
After experimenting and testing the product I decide to join forces with Coral Detection Systems as I feel that their product, the Coral Manta 3000, provides a new and crucial layer of protection that can really change the statistics, and save so many lives. 
Check it out at: www.coraldrowningdetection.com
Drowning is a preventable tragedy, and Morgan and I are thrilled to be part of a such a revolutionary product that will save many lives. I sincerely believe that every house with a pool must have it.
@CoralDrowningDetection #coralmanta
